President Trump represented the United States at the NATO Summit and thanked the countries that have met the goal of spending 2 percent of their GDP on defense. He mentioned that the United States has spent $2.5 trillion on the military and plans to increase defense spending by $400 billion in the next three years. The Secretary General of NATO praised the progress made in defense spending and credited President Trump's leadership for the increase in Allies meeting the 2 percent guideline. Other leaders from Poland and Romania also expressed their support for NATO and the importance of burden sharing. President Trump mentioned that he canceled a news conference but will still have meetings with Italy and Denmark.